  <section id="sect-00014">
  <title>Adverse Effects and Contraindications</title>
  <para id="para-00023">Common adverse effects include the following:</para>
  <list list-type="bulleted" id="list-00005">
  <item>Rash or skin reactions—pruritis and hives</item>
  <item>Gastrointestinal symptoms—nausea and vomiting</item>
  <item>Liver toxicity—jaundice, dark urine, abdominal pain, fatigue</item>
  <item>Bone marrow suppression—decreased white blood cell, red blood cell, and platelet production leading to unexplained fever, sore throat, easy bruising, bleeding, and fatigue</item>
  <item>Hypothyroidism—increased fatigue, weight gain, cold intolerance, constipation</item>
  </list>
  <para id="para-00024">Contraindications include hypersensitivity to the drug or any of its components, severe liver disease or impairment, and with pregnancy or breastfeeding because the drugs can cross the placenta, be excreted in breast milk, and potentially affect the development of the fetus or infant.</para>
